  "market_context": "Intraday session following Asia/London range; price approached and swept the previous day high (PDH at 4551.0) around 10:00 AM EST, coinciding with news release. After the sweep, price formed a bearish displacement below a prior low, confirming a market structure shift.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the previous day high (4551.0) without closing above it, then aggressively displaced lower through a prior swing low, forming a valid bearish market structure shift with high resistance liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified the previous day high (PDH) at 4551.0 as a key higher-time-frame level and marked it on the 5-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed price rising to PDH around 10:00 AM EST, forming a long upper wick candle that did not close above PDH—indicating rejection and a liquidity sweep of buy-side stops.",
    "Step 3: Watched for structural break: confirmed market structure shift when price formed aggressive full-bodied candles closing below the prior swing low (not the initial low), creating a fair value gap and displacement.",
    "Step 4: Identified confluence zone: a fair value gap, breaker block, and Fibonacci OTE (0.705–0.79 retracement) aligned near 4552–4557, forming a high-probability short entry zone.",
    "Step 5: Waited for price to retest the confluence zone (OTE within FVG and breaker block), then observed displacement downward from that zone with body respecting the breaker block and FVG."
  ],
  "outcome": "Short trade taken at retest of OTE/FVG/breaker block confluence (~4554), targeting lower swing low; price displaced lower confirming the setup.",
  "lessons": "A sweep of PDH without closure above it is a strong bearish signal when followed by displacement below structure. Valid MSS requires both liquidity sweep and aggressive close beyond prior swing—confluence of FVG, breaker block, and OTE increases entry precision and probability.",
